                    <sourcexml>LEGDOC[@legtype="bill"]</sourcexml> and
                    <sourcexml>docinfo:selector</sourcexml> having value <b>"Bills"</b>.</p>
            <p>
                <sourcexml>LEGDOC@legtype="bill"</sourcexml> becomes
                <targetxml>billtrack:billtrack[@bill-type="bill"]</targetxml> and is the root element for bills
                attributes are populated as follows: <sourcexml>LEGDOC[@id]</sourcexml> becomes
                    <targetxml>billtrack:billtrack[@xml:id]</targetxml> and provides a unique identifier for
                this element. The presence or absence of attribute value will not affect delivery
                product behavior and default value is 'none'. </p>
            <p>
                <sourcexml>LEGDOC[@legtype="bill"]</sourcexml> becomes
                    <targetxml>billtrack:billtrack[@bill-type="bill"]</targetxml>
                <pre>
                   &lt;LEGDOC legtype="bill"&gt; 
                   </pre>
                <b>becomes</b>
                <pre>
                   &lt;billtrack:billtrack bill-type="bill"&gt;    
                 </pre>
            </p>                
                                 
                    
                <p>
                <targetxml>billtrack:head</targetxml>, <targetxml>billtrack:body</targetxml>, and <targetxml>doc:metadata</targetxml> are created as
                required children of <targetxml>billtrack:billtrack</targetxml>
